Germany will play Spain in Sunday's  final of the World Team Cup after Bernd Karbacher sealed an unbeatable lead  over the United States here on Saturday.
He beat Michael Chang 6-4 6-2 following Michael Stich's 3-6 7-6 (9/7) 6-2  win over world number one Pete Sampras in the blue group.
Spain beat Sweden 3-0 in the red group.
